\"to\": 2371}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday evening\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2443}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We owe it to this French spirit.\\\"\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9996448040718878, \"rank\": 0.00030217903629869085, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"added Attal, who made it made clear that he disagreed with Macron's decision to call the surprise elections.\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2540, \"end\": 2546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8725010792775772e-44, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"added Attal\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2492}, {\"ngram\": \"the surprise elections\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hisoffer to resignafter the second round of voting was nonetheless refused by Macron.\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8725010792775772e-44, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hisoffer\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2599}, {\"ngram\": \"the second round\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2631}, {\"ngram\": \"voting\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2641}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, Macron asked Attal, whom he named as prime minister just seven months ago, to carry on at the head of a caretaker government until a coalition is formed, \\\"in order to ensure the country's stability.\\\"\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8725010792775772e-44, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Attal\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2704}, {\"ngram\": \"prime minister\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2737}, {\"ngram\": \"the head\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2784}, {\"ngram\": \"a caretaker government\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2810}, {\"ngram\": \"a coalition\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2828}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's stability\", \"from\": 2860, \"to\": 2883}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because no one won a majority of seats,Francehas what's known as a hung parliament.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2970, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2901}, {\"ngram\": \"a majority\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2916}, {\"ngram\": \"seats\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2925}, {\"ngram\": \"a hung parliament\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means the parties will have to work together - either informally or as part of a coalition - if they want to get anything done.\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the parties\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2993}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"a coalition\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3066}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's far from certain whether they will be able to do this.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3164, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As in the United States, French politics is polarized over issues such as immigration and taxes.\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3175, \"end\": 3188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997767877639004, \"rank\": 0.0002232620710263627, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3190, \"end\": 3196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9996448040718878, \"rank\": 0.00030217903629869085, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3230}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"taxes\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3260}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And unlike in neighboringGermanyand elsewhere, there is no culture of bipartisan power-sharing here.\", \"from\": 3262, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no culture\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3328}, {\"ngram\": \"bipartisan power-sharing\", \"from\": 3332, \"to\": 3356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's partly because the French system was designed so that the prime minister and Parliament would enforce the will of the more powerful president, according to Jonathan Eyal, international director at the Royal United Services Institute, a London-based think tank.\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3390, \"end\": 3396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9996448040718878, \"rank\": 0.00030217903629869085, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"]